      "id": "PopularPost370389",
      "post_content": "I can forgive any troll for having hexproof. Other stuff, not so much. Thrun is really good, but not \"Ha ha! Now you die!\" good, like many other, stupider, mythic rares. He still interacts with the opponent because he will be attacking or blocking and has no built in evasion. I feel this is an example of good design. Had hexproof been treated cautiously, like it was in Scars and earlier, things wouldn't have gotten so out of hand (looking at you, Invisible Stalker). If hexproof sticks around, it should be relatively rare, and only for green. Creatures are so squishy and fragile, and green relies upon them so heavily. Thrun has great art, but I don't have to tell you that. Also, check out that cane. I bet he was a pimp before all the fine troll ladies died, or whatever. \"Where's daddy's money, troe? I know you regenerate! Don't make me get my staff all covered in yo' nasty troll stank.\" 5/5",
